  "decision_conditions": [
    "The number of pupils at the school shall not exceed 80 at any one time.",
    "REASON",
    "To protect the Green Belt from inappropriate development caused by over intensification of the sites use, to ensure that the proposed development does not have an adverse effect upon the local highways network, and to protect neighbouring amenities in accordance with Policy DMT 2, DMT 6, DMHB 11, DMEI 4, Policy T4 of the London Plan (2021) and section 13 of the NPPF (2021).",
    "The 2 portable cabins hereby permitted shall be removed from the site within 3 months of the site ceasing to operate as a school.",
    "REASON",
    "To protect the Green Belt from inappropriate development in accordance with Policy DMEI 4 of the Hillingdon Local Plan Part 2 (2020) and section 13 of the NPPF (2021).",
    "The parking and turning scheme approved under application No.26758/APP/2019/3689 shall be carried out and completed in accordance with the approved timetable and shall remain in place for as long as the site operates as a school.",
    "REASON",
    "To ensure that the proposed development does not have an adverse effect upon the local highways network in accordance with Policy DMT 2, DMT 6 of the Hillingdon Local Plan Part 2 (2020) and Policy T4 of the London Plan (2021).",
    "The travel management scheme, travel management measures and Action Plan outlined in 'Inglenook, SIPSON LANE, WEST DRAYTON -  Travel Plan, Version 1' dated August 2021 and received 16/06/22 shall be applied and put into place prior to the pupil increase. The travel measures and plans should be adhered to and shall remain in place for as long as the site operates as a school.",
    "REASON",
    "To ensure that the proposed development does not have an adverse effect upon the local highways network in accordance with Policy DMT 2 of the Hillingdon Local Plan Part 2 (2020) and Policy T4 of the London Plan (2021).",
    "The decision to GRANT planning permission has been taken having regard to all relevant planning legislation, regulations, guidance, circulars and Council policies, including The Human Rights Act (1998) (HRA 1998) which makes it unlawful for the Council to act incompatibly with Convention rights, specifically Article 6 (right to a fair hearing); Article 8 (right to respect for private and family life); Article 1 of the First Protocol (protection of property) and Article 14 (prohibition of discrimination).",
    "The decision to GRANT planning permission has been taken having regard to the policies and proposals in the Hillingdon Local Plan Part 1 (2012) and Part 2 (2020) set out below, including Supplementary Planning Guidance, and to all relevant material considerations, including The London Plan (2021)."
  ],
